reviews.headline: Affordable + multi purpose
reviews.comments: I love the smell & I use it as a detangler after washing my hair , & as a heat protectant spray before blowdrying or curling. The only con is limited supply when I go to the store

reviews.headline: I will always repurchase this
reviews.comments: I love how well this protects my hair from heat as well as detangles as a bonus it smells amazing but not overpowering

reviews.headline: On my 50th bottle
reviews.comments: I buy this everytime it goes on sale. I wish there was a perfume that smelled like this spray. I use it everytime I dry my hair. The only con that I've noticed is that it leaks a little from the handle when being sprayed.

reviews.headline: Old fan, hate the new formula
reviews.comments: They have to have changed the formula. It used to be so lightweight but still hydrating, and super affordable. it now costs more and I hate it at least for my hair. My hair is fine but there is a lot of it and it is straight. This formula feels like a weird dry oil? it made my hair look greasy even when I only used a tiny bit. in the past I have bought this heat protector at least 5 times and would douse my hair in it to protect it thoroughly with no such issue. im so sad because now I have to return this and start over. I only gave it a second star because it still smells great (think forever sunshine from b&bw circa 2010) and maybe it is good for a different hair texture now?

reviews.headline: I love this!
reviews.comments: Definitely would buy again! Was recommended by Jenn and my hair is so much better now and less frizzy also so smooth!

reviews.headline: Daily staple
reviews.comments: I have fine but long hair and i've been using the original version for probably 6+ years now (this is the 3rd redesign of the bottle ive seen). I use this pretty liberally from mid shaft down after i get out of the shower. The smell is incredible and it just makes my hair feel better and healthier. Is it an absolute necessity? No. But when i run out and dont have it, i can tell because my hair is so dry. I prefer this over hair oil.

reviews.headline: Love love love!
reviews.comments: I always recommend this to my friends! Ive been using this product for yearsss. Love that it protects my hair from sun damage, heat damage, and spit ends/ breakage. Also great smell and detangler

reviews.headline: Love love love!
reviews.comments: I always recommend this to my friends! Ive been using this product for yearsss. Love that it protects my hair from sun damage, heat damage, and spit ends/ breakage. Also great smell and detangler

reviews.headline: Can't Go Without This
reviews.comments: I use this on my wavy hair and one of my daughters' very curly hair. It protects, adds shine, and does not make our hair brittle.

reviews.headline: Bottle leaked everywhere
reviews.comments: The bottle leaked all over everything when it was shipped. Then I tried to use it and it was even worse. Hopefully their new bottle is better but I'm stuck with old bottle that leaks and drips on the floor.  Wasted product for sure

reviews.headline: Will re-purchase

reviews.headline: Great for frizz
reviews.comments: Great for frizz caused by humidity.  Doesn't leave a greasy look like some products.

reviews.headline: The sprayer doesn't leak anymore!
reviews.comments: It's not my favorite but it'll get the job done. I'm just glad the sprayer doesn't leak the oil anymore (I've probably owned 5 over the years and they all did). My hair is treated and just needs a little more than this offers but I loved it when my hair was natural.

reviews.headline: I didn't like it
reviews.comments: I didn't like how it made hair feel after it dried. It felt kinda greasy.

reviews.headline: Yes!
reviews.comments: It doesn't leak!

reviews.headline: Second time buying it.
reviews.comments: Second time buying this product. Absolutely love that it protects my hair from heat when styling but I also love how it leaves my hair when I don't style it. Does a wonderful job untangling my hair. The new packaging is an upgrade since it doesn't leak any product, like old one. My only complaint is that the new bottle holds a bit less product (5 FL OZ) than the old one (5.4 FL OZ), wish they would've left the same amount of product and new packaging.

reviews.headline: Very heavy & fragrant
reviews.comments: I was so excited to use this but it makes my thick, wavy hair so heavy! I used it very sparingly but it still weighs down my hair so much and felt very icky. It has a very strong smell - while it smells good, it's way too strong. Very disappointed in this product and confused why it's so highly rated!

faceoff_negative.comments:
I purchased this product based in large part on the overwhelmingly positive reviews. I used this on already clean and dry hair to prepare and "prime" for my flat iron. I did a test spray on my hand and noticed the product came out in a fist, clear mist. The consistency felt quite oily/ "slippy" on my hand. I felt like I would need to use this product sparingly because in my prior experience, this type of product often left a greasy film or residue on my hair, even after styling. With this in mind, I sprayed a couple sprays (2 - 3) in my mid-lengths and ends. I carefully avoided my roots. 

As I straightened/ styled, I didn't notice any sort of steaming or anything coming off of the hair or iron which can sometimes happen. I also did not notice any odor or smell of burnt hair. These appeared to be favorable signs. 

The product lays out 10 benefits/ claims: 
Strengthens
Heat Protection 
Reduces Frizz
Detangles
Softens 
Cuts Drying Time
Adds Shine 
Nourishes 
Smooths 
UV Protection

I cannot really speak to whether the product has UV protection, or strengthens since I haven't used it for very long. I will say that I think this isn't the right product for me. It gives me very greasy, oily hair that is weighed down even when I apply it to the ends/ mids alone. I didn't really see a whole lot of frizz reduction with this product either. If it works for you, great, but I don't actually see anything revolutionary about this product. It might provide some heat protection, but again, there are other products on the market that do that just as well and better, are more affordable, and do not weigh the hair down. 

The ingredient list is not long: 
Isododecane (it is derived from petroleum products)
Isopropyl Palmitate (Isopropyl palmitate is the ester of isopropyl alcohol and palmitic acid. It is an emollient, moisturizer, thickening agent, and anti-static agent) 
Isohexadecane (synthetic ingredient used as a cleansing agent, solvent, texture enhancer, and skin-conditioning agent.)
Ethylhexyl Olivate (an olive-derived emollient. More specifically, it is the natural ester of skin-conditioning fatty acids derived from olive oil) 
Argania Spinosa (Argan) Kernel Oil (argan oil, pretty self-explanatory) 
Helianthus Annuus (Sunflower) Seed Oil (self-explanatory)
Squalane (fairly common moisturizer, also tends to be greasy/ oily) 
Fragrance (Top:‚Äã Freesia, Plum‚Äã. Heart:‚Äã White Flowers (Jasmine, Magnolia, Gardenia)‚Äã. Dry Down:‚Äã Woody Warm Amber, Bourbon Vanilla, White Musk)

As you can probably see from the list above, this product is chock full of a lot of greasy/ oily ingredients that will give the hair a lot of slip, which is why is may be helpful for detangling. There isn't anything inherently heat protective about this product and the oils may weigh your hair down.  A few heat-protecting ingredients have been studied independently to reveal their efficacy, specifically PVP/DMAPA acrylates copolymer, quaternium-70, and hydrolyzed wheat protein. This product contains none of those. 

Looking at EWG, this product scores a 4 of 10, with a high risk for Allergies & Immunotoxicity because of CYCLOPENTASILOXANE.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not really sure about this.
